radiographic_examinations.findings: Subcentimeter hypodense lesion in the left lobe of the liver likely represents a cyst or biliary hamartoma; no evidence of intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation; gallbladder is normal; normal pancreas, spleen, adrenals, kidneys; diverticulosis of the sigmoid colon; dilation of the fluid-filled appendix measuring up to 9 mm with mild surrounding fat stranding; no evidence of perforation or abscess; multiple ventral abdominal wall fat containing hernias.
